==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outmantle
<hw>Out*man"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To excel in
mantling; hence, to excel in splendor, as of dress.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And with poetic trappings grace thy prose,⟦br⟧
Till it <qex>outmantle</qex> all the pride of verse.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outmarch</ent>⟦br⟧
